item.description:
This is the polished version of the i3resizemode script i made in one of the Lets Linux episodes. I named it after the moderator on up who banned me for a month after I told a guy to RTFM&hellip;
i3Kornhe - Resize windows by moving the corners. SYNOPSIS i3Kornhe [-v|-h] DIRECTION
DESCRIPTION The script checks if the currently active window is floating. If it is floating the script will acrivate one of four modes depending on the direction.

This is a helper script that copies and resizes an image and move it to the correct directory for use on my website, budlabs.
img4site - Adds image(s) to the budlabs site SYNOPSIS img4site [-v|-h] -s|FILE &hellip;
DESCRIPTION img4site copies IMAGE to budlabs and if needed also creates a resized copie of the image. If -s is passed a screenshot will be taken and used as FILE. A hugo shortcode for the image will be put in the clipboard and selection after succesful operation.
